    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it’s not just a 'moment' though. it’s the whole foundation. i lived my whole life being the one who had it together, the one who never failed. now that's gone. the version of me that people actually cared about is literally gone. i'm just standing here in the ruins of who i was. what's even the point of trying to 'heal' a person that doesn't exist anymore?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is completely understandable to feel like the loss of your old self is an existential crisis. Healing isn't about recreating who you were, but about giving yourself permission to build something new, even if it starts small. The \"you\" that remains is capable of growth and learning from this painful transition. Please allow yourself compassion as you navigate this profound sense of loss; you don't have to find the \"point\" right now, just take the next small step.",
      "source": "target",
